      "content": "ok i get the \"climbing rope\" thing. so to be more specific, how does the actual physical shape of the rebar help with this? i've seen some rebar that has these little bumps or ridges on it instead of just being a smooth cylinder. is that just for the grip you mentioned, and what happens if the bond fails inside the slab?",
